TITLE: Netflix earnings are after the bell. Here's what to expect
SUMMARY: Netflix reports first-quarter earnings after the closing bell Thursday.

TITLE: Harvard's battle with the Trump administration is creating a thorny financial situation
SUMMARY: Even for America's richest university, covering federal funding cuts is no small task.

TITLE: American Express’s wealthy cardholders are mostly untouched by tariff jitters
SUMMARY: American Express results show that the company's wealthier customers may insulate it somewhat from concerns that tariffs and stubborn inflation have caused.

TITLE: UnitedHealth's stock is plunging on higher medical costs. That may mean trouble for more insurers
SUMMARY: The warning sign from a health-care giant seen as the insurance industry's bellwether may mean trouble for companies with Medicare Advantage plans.

TITLE: Target CEO Cornell to meet with Sharpton to discuss DEI rollback as civil rights leader considers boycott
SUMMARY: Target CEO Brian Cornell will meet with the Rev. Al Sharpton as the company contends with a slump in foot traffic after walking back some DEI initiatives.

SUMMARY: The results bring Eli Lilly's pill orforglipron one step closer to becoming a new, needle-free alternative in the booming weight loss and diabetes market.

TITLE: Chinese tea chain Chagee climbs 20% in stock market debut
SUMMARY: Chagee, a Chinese tea chain, made its U.S. public market debut on the Nasdaq as trade tensions between Washington and Beijing rise.

TITLE: Wall Street trading desks are feasting on the volatility from Trump’s global upheaval
SUMMARY: The six biggest U.S. banks put up $16.3 billion in stock trading revenue, 33% more year over year and higher than the 2020 pandemic or the 2008 financial crisis.

TITLE: Nissan aims to 'max out' U.S. production plant amid Trump's tariffs
SUMMARY: Nissan 6-million-square-foot facility in Smyrna, Tennessee, is capable of producing 640,000 vehicles a year on three shifts, Meunier said.

TITLE: Proposed SNAP cuts could pressure low-income shoppers — and retailers that serve them
SUMMARY: Potential changes to the federal food assistance program could impact millions of U.S. shoppers, retailers and food and beverage companies.

TITLE: JPMorgan Chase sues more customers who allegedly stole cash in 'infinite money glitch'
SUMMARY: The episode highlights the lengths JPMorgan Chase, the biggest U.S. bank by assets, will go to claw back funds it is owed and to deter future crimes.

SUMMARY: Supplies of new and used vehicles for sale are declining rapidly as consumers flock to stores ahead of potential price increases due to tariffs.

SUMMARY: Heineken shrugged off the threat of tariffs earlier this year, but in the company's latest earnings report, it said it's becoming increasingly cautious.

SUMMARY: Medical technology and device makers are fighting for tariff exemptions, while PPE makers are applauding the levies.

TITLE: CBP says latest tariffs have generated $500 million, well below Trump's estimate
SUMMARY: Trump has repeatedly said the United States is taking in $2 billion per day from tariffs.

TITLE: Universal's new Epic Universe park set to generate $2 billion for Florida in year one
SUMMARY: Epic Universe is not only expected to bolster theme park revenues for Universal, but it will also bring in billions of dollars to the local economy.

TITLE: Bank of America tops analysts' estimates on better-than-expected interest income, trading
SUMMARY: Bank of America shares have sold off in recent weeks on concern that President Donald Trump's tariff policies could cause a recession.

TITLE: Citigroup results exceed analysts' estimates on gains in fixed income and equities trading
SUMMARY: CEO Jane Fraser said Tuesday that the bank was continuing to earn credibility with investors and that she remains focused on executing on her strategy.

TITLE: American Airlines to make Wi-Fi free on most of its fleet in 2026
SUMMARY: American Airlines is following other airlines such as Delta and JetBlue in making Wi-Fi free on board.

SUMMARY: The comments pushed stocks such as Ford, GM and Chrysler parent Stellantis higher, swinging from trading levels or negative to being up between 1% and 4%.

TITLE: Goldman Sachs tops estimates on boom in equities trading revenue
SUMMARY: Goldman Sachs joins rivals JPMorgan Chase and Morgan Stanley in posting better-than-expected equities trading revenue.

TITLE: Pfizer scraps daily weight loss pill after liver injury in one patient

TITLE: GM cutting jobs, idling Canadian electric van plant due to 'market demand'

TITLE: Trump's pharmaceutical tariffs could raise costs for patients, worsen drug shortages
SUMMARY: It's unclear whether tariffs will influence more companies to make more drugs in the U.S. like President Donald Trump is hoping for, some experts said.
